The paper discusses the pattern formation problem for mobile robots, which falls under the multi-agent systems (cs.MA) sub-category. The focus is on the gathering problem, which is a common problem in robotics and falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of unreliable compasses, which falls under the distributed computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper discusses synchronous, semi-synchronous, and asynchronous models, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes algorithms to solve the gathering problem, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
